        {
            "paragraph": 3,
            "sentance_id": 20,
            "sentence_md5": "6ee711f3a51849473d3dcbc3c59d31cd",
            "sentance": "It’s almost as though we have to outdo other people to achieve our own goals.",
            "phonetic": "/ɪts ˈɔːlməʊst æz ðəʊ wi hæv tə ˌaʊtˈduː ˈʌðə(r) ˈpiːpl tə əˈtʃiːv aʊə(r) əʊn ɡəʊlz./",
            "translation": "就好像我们必须超越别人才能实现我们自己的目标。",
            "audio_file": "data/audio/6ee711f3a51849473d3dcbc3c59d31cd.mp3",
            "analysis": {
                "long_sentence_analysis": "",
                "core_vocabulary": [
                    {
                        "word": "outdo",
                        "phonetic": "/ˌaʊtˈduː/",
                        "meaning": "v. 胜过，超越"
                    }
                ],
                "phrases": [
                    {
                        "phrase": "as though",
                        "meaning": "仿佛，好像"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "paragraph": 4,
            "sentance_id": 21,
            "sentence_md5": "4ae233b1c9523b202d7556adf63ae21d",
            "sentance": "Edward Wynne, editor of a magazine blames the rise in academic dishonesty on the schools.",
            "phonetic": "/ˈedwəd wɪn, ˈedɪtə(r) ɒv ə ˌmæɡəˈziːn bleɪmz ðə raɪz ɪn ˌækəˈdemɪk dɪsˈɒnɪsti ɒn ðə skuːlz./",
            "translation": "一家杂志的主编爱德华·温将学术不诚实行为的上升归咎于学校。",
            "audio_file": "data/audio/4ae233b1c9523b202d7556adf63ae21d.mp3",
            "analysis": {
                "long_sentence_analysis": "",
                "core_vocabulary": [],
                "phrases": []
            }
        },
        {
            "paragraph": 4,
            "sentance_id": 22,
            "sentence_md5": "ed4d9c9ea8dd224035554a019e52fef8",
            "sentance": "He claims that administrators and teachers have been too hesitant to take action.",
            "phonetic": "/hi kleɪmz ðæt ədˈmɪnɪstreɪtəz ænd ˈtiːtʃəz həv biːn tuː ˈhezɪtənt tə teɪk ˈækʃn./",
            "translation": "他声称管理者和老师在采取行动方面过于犹豫不决。",
            "audio_file": "data/audio/ed4d9c9ea8dd224035554a019e52fef8.mp3",
            "analysis": {
                "long_sentence_analysis": "",
                "core_vocabulary": [
                    {
                        "word": "hesitant",
                        "phonetic": "/ˈhezɪtənt/",
                        "meaning": "adj. 犹豫的"
                    }
                ],
                "phrases": []
            }
        },
        {
            "paragraph": 4,
            "sentance_id": 23,
            "sentence_md5": "301633dab1ccddc9cff87f8ed0962706",
            "sentance": "Dwight Huber, chairman of the English department at Amarillo sees the matter differently, blaming the rise in cheating on the way students are evaluated.",
            "phonetic": "/dwaɪt ˈhjuːbə(r), ˈtʃeəmən ɒv ðə ˈɪŋɡlɪʃ dɪˈpɑːtmənt æt Amarillo siːz ðə ˈmætə(r) ˈdɪfrəntli, ˈbleɪmɪŋ ðə raɪz ɪn ˈtʃiːtɪŋ ɒn ðə weɪ ˈstjuːdnts ɑː(r) ɪˈvæljueɪtɪd./",
            "translation": "阿马里洛高中英语系主任德怀特·胡伯对这件事有不同看法，他把作弊的上升归咎于评估学生的方式。",
            "audio_file": "data/audio/301633dab1ccddc9cff87f8ed0962706.mp3",
            "analysis": {
                "long_sentence_analysis": "blaming ... 为分词做伴随状语",
                "core_vocabulary": [],
                "phrases": []
            }
        },
        {
            "paragraph": 4,
            "sentance_id": 24,
            "sentence_md5": "d56e194257ef55652d89df027022469e",
            "sentance": "“I would cheat if I felt I was being cheated,” Mr. huber said.",
            "phonetic": "/aɪ wʊd tʃiːt ɪf aɪ felt aɪ wəz ˈbiːɪŋ ˈtʃiːtɪd, ˈmɪstə(r) ˈhjuːbə(r) sed./",
            "translation": "“如果我觉得我被欺骗了，我就会作弊，”胡伯先生说。",
            "audio_file": "data/audio/d56e194257ef55652d89df027022469e.mp3",
            "analysis": {
                "long_sentence_analysis": "",
                "core_vocabulary": [],
                "phrases": []
            }
        },
        {
            "paragraph": 4,
            "sentance_id": 25,
            "sentence_md5": "81c27c37d5e754b1f891a526eec0cc6f",
            "sentance": "He feels that as long as teachers give short-answer tests rather than essay questions and rate students by the number of facts they can memorize rather than by how well they can synthesize information, students will try to beat the system.",
            "phonetic": "/hi fiːlz ðæt æz lɒŋ æz ˈtiːtʃəz ɡɪv ʃɔːt-ˈɑːnsə(r) tests ˈrɑːðə(r) ðæn ˈeseɪ ˈkwestʃənz ænd reɪt ˈstjuːdnts baɪ ðə ˈnʌmbə(r) ɒv fækts ðeɪ kæn ˈmeməraɪz ˈrɑːðə(r) ðæn baɪ haʊ wel ðeɪ kæn ˈsɪnθəsaɪz ˌɪnfəˈmeɪʃn, ˈstjuːdnts wɪl traɪ tə biːt ðə ˈsɪstəm./",
            "translation": "他认为，只要老师给出简答题而不是论述题，并通过学生能记住的事实数量而不是他们能综合信息的程度来评估学生，学生就会试图寻找系统漏洞。",
            "audio_file": "data/audio/81c27c37d5e754b1f891a526eec0cc6f.mp3",
            "analysis": {
                "long_sentence_analysis": "主句是students will try to beat the system。前面包含了as long as引导的条件状语从句",
                "core_vocabulary": [
                    {
                        "word": "synthesize",
                        "phonetic": "/ˈsɪnθəsaɪz/",
                        "meaning": "v. 综合"
                    }
                ],
                "phrases": []
            }
        },
        {
            "paragraph": 4,
